1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,080
(Previously)
Congrats on leaking the news.

2
00:00:03,104 --> 00:00:09,536
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

3
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:06,100
But this crap can't hurt me.

4
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,660
You do like to brag.

5
00:00:09,060 --> 00:00:11,100
You told your mom
you got the lead role in the play.

6
00:00:11,140 --> 00:00:12,940
I never told my mom I had the lead.

7
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,840
I know I'm just a supporting character.

8
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:17,240
No matter what I do,
my mom will never be proud of me.

9
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:18,280
Hey.

10
00:00:18,281 --> 00:00:19,956
I've pulled every kind of
stubborn stunt with my family.

11
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:22,580
If you insist on saying no,
what can anyone do to you?

12
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,120
Do you still love me?

13
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:25,640
You got your answer?

14
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,200
How long have you and Tua been close?

15
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:29,860
You two don't look like you're friends.

16
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:31,300
Looks like something else.

17
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:32,980
Stop making Tua uncomfortable.

18
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:34,060
He doesn't like you.

19
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:40,280
If you've got something better to offer me,
I might change my mind.

20
00:00:41,820 --> 00:00:42,820
Leave Tua alone.

21
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,300
(Episode 5: Super Objective)

22
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,080
I'll get going then.

23
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,760
Hold on.

24
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,040
Can we talk inside for a bit?

25
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,640
Are you still drunk?

26
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,920
I sobered up before we left the studio.

27
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,160
So…

28
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,760
You agreed to model for Boston

29
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,520
because… you didn't want
him messing with me?

30
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,360
Mm.

31
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,480
That's all?

32
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,520
I just don't like people
treating you badly.

33
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,440
And you kissed me

34
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,360
because you didn't want
Boston messing with me too?

35
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,800
Well…

36
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:09,880
I…

37
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,880
Do you remember that night?

38
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,720
At the party, when we kissed.

39
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,560
I lied to you.

40
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:29,880
I wasn't just teasing you
or helping you rehearse for the play.

41
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,760
I wanted to know how you felt about me.

42
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:51,960
Tua.

43
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,080
I can't give you an answer

44
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:59,080
because I don't know
what this feeling for you is.

45
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,520
But I like you, Arnold.

46
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,440
Now that you know,

47
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,200
do you hate me?

48
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,960
Take time to figure out

49
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,360
how you feel about me.

50
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:18,200
"Only Friends : Dream On"

51
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:52,120
I LEFT. YOU WERE SLEEPING PEACEFULLY.
DIDN'T WANNA WAKE YOU.

52
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:36,680
Mm… interesting project.

53
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:41,120
Hey, is that Arnold?

54
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:43,600
I see him on TikTok a lot.

55
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:46,800
It's adorable when he dances.
He has quite a following.

56
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,440
That's true.

57
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Hey!

58
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,079
Isn't that Little Raffy, Ranchalee's son?

59
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,119
You know them?

60
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:57,120
Mhm. She's my
all-time favorite leading actress.

61
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,640
I just saw him on a show
with his mom the other day.

62
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,880
It was so lovely.

63
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:09,400
There are a bunch of
talented people in this project.

64
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,560
Mm. Interesting.

65
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:17,400
Celebrities like them
can be a magnet for sponsors.

66
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,640
Actors.

67
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,400
Jack.

68
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:31,800
I hope you'll support
the university production, Ms. Yui.

69
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:34,680
If you have any concerns,
please let me know.

70
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,160
Mm.

71
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:42,520
Why not give the lead role
to a famous actress's son?

72
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:49,040
He's very well-known, I think
you could attract plenty of sponsors.

73
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,720
We have our own process.

74
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:56,440
Every actor has to go through auditions.

75
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:59,720
The actors we selected
are the most suitable for their roles.

76
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:07,040
A good performance with no audience…

77
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,760
I don't see why I should fund it.

78
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:20,760
Why not make Little Raffy the lead? Hm?

79
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:26,960
If someone with a large following
and that level of fame takes the role,

80
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:31,640
the project would be worth sponsoring.

81
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:44,280
I don't agree.

82
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:47,080
If that's how she sees it,
we should find another sponsor.

83
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,920
Jack, I've been looking for a while.

84
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,920
I'm sure there are other people
who might be interested.

85
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:58,959
Look. This is the last company
showing interest in our play.

86
00:10:58,960 --> 00:10:59,960
We still have time.

87
00:10:59,961 --> 00:11:02,320
Jack, we don't have much time.

88
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:06,680
If you turn her down and rely on funds
from the Fine Arts Fair alone,

89
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,560
we won't get much.

90
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:17,400
I know it's difficult,
and I don't want this to happen either.

91
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:24,879
But as the producer, if giving in benefits
the project, we should consider it.

92
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,400
But that's not fair to our actors.

93
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:29,440
What do you expect me to tell Dean?

94
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,880
You'll have to find a way to talk to him.

95
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:51,639
Little Raf has always
been confident in front of people.

96
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:57,360
I had him take acting, singing,
and music classes when he was little.

97
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,680
What about you, Little Raf?

98
00:11:58,681 --> 00:12:00,719
Are you planning to
follow in your mom's footsteps…

99
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,640
So, you've been helping Jack
with his stage play?

100
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,680
His mom told me.

101
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,360
I'm helping with the sound.

102
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,280
Shouldn't you be focusing on your DJ work?

103
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,080
I am.

104
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,400
Then why are you helping someone else?

105
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,320
I'm not doing this for someone else.

106
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,640
I'm doing it for myself.

107
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,880
Can you not put pressure on me?

108
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:26,920
I'm not. But look at Jack.

109
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,440
Whatever he does, he gives it his all.

110
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,040
Just don't disappoint me.

111
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,440
Hey. What's up?

112
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:03,360
How did the meeting with the sponsor go?

113
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:04,920
Did they give us 200K?

114
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,720
Hm?

115
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,720
Why are you practicing alone?

116
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,200
You know I'm not
very good with action scenes.

117
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,840
So I'm practicing to get used to them.

118
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:23,240
Besides, I want your dream play
to turn out perfect.

119
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:27,640
I told you I'd be the new Dean for you.

120
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,640
Dean.

121
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Hm?

122
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:40,160
I've got something important to tell you.

123
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:48,840
Timmy and I spoke to the sponsor.

124
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:53,760
They want lead actors
with a large following,

125
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,000
so they suggested…

126
00:13:58,640 --> 00:13:59,640
Raffy

127
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:03,960
for the lead.

128
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,120
The same role as you.

129
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,440
And?

130
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:08,920
You agreed?

131
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,360
No, I didn't.

132
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:16,640
But without sponsors,
the play won't happen.

133
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:22,280
So I was thinking you and Raffy
could alternate performances.

134
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,160
What are you even talking about?

135
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,880
I've always been the lead.

136
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:34,480
How is that any different from making me
his substitute or understudy, Jack?

137
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:37,760
I'm not cutting down your role.
I'm suggesting a double cast.

138
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,720
You used to say
the acting was what mattered most.

139
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:46,759
So how did you let the sponsor
push you into this, Jack?

140
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,080
What the hell are you thinking?

141
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,760
I don't want it to be like this either.

142
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,440
Damn it!

143
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:55,959
Dean, calm down.

144
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,000
I don't want to calm down!

145
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,520
Tell me this.

146
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:02,800
What the hell does he have over me
besides a famous mother?

147
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,999
How privileged. Being
the son of an actress.

148
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:08,360
Do talented people really have to step aside
just because someone has more followers?

149
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,640
I hope the decision I
made was the right one.

150
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,640
What?

151
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,560
I think you look quite good in person.

152
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:58,520
They dressed you ridiculously on TV.
You look much better in normal clothes.

153
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,440
What the heck are you talking about?

154
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,520
The Spotlight Tonight.

155
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,600
I watched it live.

156
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,240
Sharp features,

157
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,840
broad shoulders, nice skin…

158
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,280
But I think the camera
didn't do you justice.

159
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,840
You're way cuter in person.

160
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,920
Don't get so close.
People might get the wrong idea.

161
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,480
Where are you going,
soon-to-be rising star?

162
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,600
The casting was done fair and square.

163
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:43,720
So why the hell are
you taking my lead role?

164
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,960
Huh?

165
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:56,600
No matter the era, a nepo baby like you
always gets the privilege.

166
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:02,080
Go ahead and play the role well
and live up to your follower count.

167
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,040
What the fuck are you talking about?

168
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,121
About you stealing my role.

169
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:04,880
What role?

170
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,120
My Romeo role.

171
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,200
You don't know that? Huh?

172
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:08,840
Huh?
Don't fucking play dumb.

173
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,479
Stop. Knock it off.
When did I ever do that?

174
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,679
That's enough. Stop!
I'm not stopping!

175
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,719
Dean! I said that's enough!

176
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,360
No!
Listen to me!

177
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:21,080
Dean's making a scene,
saying I stole his role.

178
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,880
Raffy, I was about to tell you.

179
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,600
From now on, we'll do a double cast.

180
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,440
You'll share the role with Dean.

181
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,560
Hi, Tua.

182
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,040
I got you a burger.

183
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,960
I figured you might not have eaten yet.

184
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,280
Thank you.

185
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:28,400
So… you said you didn't know before.

186
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,120
Have you figured it out now?

187
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,520
Huh?

188
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:35,720
Figured what out?

189
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,560
About… our status.

190
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,200
Ah.

191
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:49,760
Um…

192
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:56,400
To be honest, I still
can't give you an answer.

193
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,600
Would that bother you?

194
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:08,840
No.

195
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,440
I just want to know where I stand.

196
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:18,080
If we're in a situationship,
I'm fine with that.

197
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:23,320
But if you ever have a clear answer,
let me know.

198
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,800
Just don't let it turn
into a situation-shit.

199
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,320
Thank you, Tua.

200
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:42,960
If you're really okay with it,
we can just keep things like this for now.

201
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:58,760
Oh.

202
00:19:58,840 --> 00:19:59,840
Hey, Tua.

203
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:01,800
Tua.

204
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,120
Wait.

205
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,160
Don't eat that.

206
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,640
Here. Eat with me.

207
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,400
Look at you.

208
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,080
Without me, how are you going to survive?

209
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,440
I'll survive.

210
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:23,600
Of course I will.

211
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,720
I can't make up my mind.

212
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,880
I'm afraid if I cross the line
and it doesn't work out,

213
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:45,440
things will get awkward between us.

214
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:50,960
What we have now is good.

215
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:56,560
But if we were more, it'd be clearer.

216
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,560
Dean, can you just hear me out?

217
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:22,040
If this were only my play,
I would never let this happen.

218
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:23,880
But it's not.

219
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:29,600
Given my position and my duties,
I have to look at the bigger picture.

220
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:36,040
So what? Hm?

221
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:39,040
Couldn't you have done better?

222
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,040
Couldn't you negotiate with them at all?

223
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,200
Huh?

224
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,760
I tried everything.

225
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:46,240
The play could've been canceled.

226
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,200
We might not get to perform even once.

227
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,240
Dean.

228
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:05,680
No matter what happens,
you're still my number one actor.

229
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:17,120
Okay.

230
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:19,920
I get it now.

231
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,720
Mm.

232
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:30,240
So, what matters
is the number of followers, right?

233
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,200
Fine.

234
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,360
I'll get that for you.

235
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,720
Just watch me.

236
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,520
May I join you?

237
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,240
About the double cast, I'm sorry.

238
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:53,560
To be honest, I don't like
getting the role under those conditions.

239
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:57,080
But I understand the sponsor's position.

240
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,200
Followers matter these days.

241
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:06,320
And I understand you too.

242
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:09,120
It's the sponsor's request, right?

243
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:14,320
Right.

244
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:22,960
Raffy.

245
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,120
You still want to help me, don't you?

246
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,720
Mhm.

247
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,120
Thank you so much.

248
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,640
Did you plan all that?

249
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:29,880
What are you on about now?

250
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,520
What did I do?

251
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,560
The opportunity came to me on its own.

252
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:37,200
Are you sure it came to you on its own?

253
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,560
Or did you steal it from someone else?

254
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,480
Believe whatever you want.

255
00:25:43,960 --> 00:25:45,440
But let me tell you something.

256
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:51,400
When I get an opportunity,
whether it's acting or Jack,

257
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,040
I'll never let it pass me by.

258
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:02,880
Even though you didn't
earn that opportunity with your skills?

259
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:10,720
Skills can be learned.

260
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,400
You believe that too, don't you?

261
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,519
You practice DJing every day.

262
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:18,560
Don't compare someone like yourself to me.

263
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,800
I know what my goal is.

264
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:24,480
But you…

265
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,240
You don't even know what you're doing.

266
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,320
Of course I do.

267
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:50,320
